Scott has been seeing an issue with the Catfish placements where the translucent black frame is displaying intermittently.  After investigating with Joel, the issue appears due to a global application of div[id*=banner_div] iframe {max_width: 970px;}  by removing that element property the black frame correctly renders (see max_width.png)


This in essence forces the max width of all “banner_divs” to assume the property regardless of their placement or purpose, effectively treating both leaderboards, jumbotron and catfish all the same.  Further tracing the source of this property call is from the main mpi.guides29.com/Content/Styles/style.css (see css.png).


This is a global page issue that should be addressed by the Thumbtack team.


High Priority - 3 


@Danil_Nikiforov

Card_Title: Guides 2.9: Reimplement design for Home Page
Card_Description:
Guides 2.0. Implement the following changes for the Home Page :


  • with the change in direction for the menu and dynamic layout, the ‘pin as nav’ button has been removed and the ‘select region’ button has been moved into it’s place to more effectively communicate the relationship between the region selection map and the headings.

  • The region select map now slides in from off canvas until fully visible to the right of the category nav with a lower z-index so that it appears to slide in from behind the menu.

  • The blue cards in the wireframe are ‘Featured Company’ slots and will remain fixed in the first row.

  • The green card is reserved for Association advertisement or branding space and must remain fixed in it’s position.

  • The yellow cards are ‘Featured Content’ slots and can be arranged by the browser wherever they may fit within the grid down to our tablet breakpoint of 1024px. (isotope is an example of what we are envisioning)

  • The red cards are ‘Vendor Showcases’ and can fit and arrange anywhere after the first row in order to fill the gaps where there are no featured content blocks loaded.

  • The grids repetition of rows should end at a count of 20 (maybe less, 10 may be more reasonable but we can experiment).

  • The responsive grid should only frame the colored blocks. 

  • All gray blocks are advertiser inventory slots. 

  • The column on the right will facilitate 300x250 ads and must remain fixed, therefore it should not be included in the responsive grid and remain as an element of its own. 

  • What used to be the top and bottom global leaderboards (90H x 100%W) will now be centered as fixed IAB 90x768 leaderboards.

  • You may use any combination of bootstrap and isotope to achieve the maximum use of real estate and resizing – we will leave this to your discretion. 

  • All else should remain as planned unless further notice.

Card_Title: Guides 2.9 - Super Leader page  FR0060 - Brand Affinity Page
Card_Description:
Functional for Super Leader page will provide MV side. In this card need to connect layout to functional.


The Adzerk code for the BrandAffinity is similar to the code for the Jumbotron, but with one exception – the ID passed to the page will be passed to the Adzerk code.  The highlighted part below is what is different for the BrandAffinity from the Jumbotron.  The rest of the variables are all the same as for the Jumbotrons.


 ados_add_placement($Env, ADZERK_SITEID, "slotName", $SlotSize).setFlightCreativeId($FlightCreativeId).setZone(JUMBOTRON_ZONE);


 


 


The $FlightCreativeId is the numerical string that’s being passed to the page.  So, a url of mpi.dev.guides29.com/brandaffinity/1421014 would have the following as the ad call:


ados_add_placement(5166, 52187, "AdzerkBrandAffinity", 123).setFlightCreativeId(1421014).setZone(150419);

Card_Title: Guides 2.9 FR0096 - implement Super Leader inventory
Card_Description:
Katrin:


I have some additional information to assist with TT’s coding of the jumbotron.


Adzerk logs the impression for the ad when the div for the request is loaded.  So if we request an ad for a div named “jumbotron2”, but the div isn’t placed on the page, the impression won’t be recorded.  If the div is placed and hidden with CSS, the impression will still be logged. 


If we wait to place the div on the page until it’s ready to be viewed by the user, that should handle the logging the way we want.


 


We have created a reference document for the creation of the Brand Affinity Page that is accessed through the Jumbotron on the Home Page. Please find the document on Sharepoint here. (Brand Affinity Flow.vsdx)


 


1.       The top leaderboard is not appearing on the page.  The parent div for leaderboard1 has a class of top-banner, which is currently set to display:none.  Please adjust the CSS so that the banner can be displayed.


2.      The code for the Jumbotron needs to be modified to control when the ads display.  Adzerk logs the impression for the ad when the div for the request is loaded.  So if we request an ad for a div named “jumbotron2”, but the div isn’t placed on the page, the impression won’t be recorded.  If the div is placed and hidden with CSS, the impression will still be logged.  If we wait to place the div on the page until it’s ready to be viewed by the user, that should handle the logging the way we want.
-----------------------------

Precondition:  Company Profile page must be setup or should contain the standard elements.

As an Advertiser, I must be able to view/access the listed data elements



  • Business Name

  • Business Status (varies by guide), may include status such as “member”, “exhibitor”, etc. (These elements should be view-only.  The filters are turned on/off via Taser).

    • Contact name

    • Contact title

    • Phone Number

    • Additional Number (E.g.: Toll Free Number)

    • Fax Number

    • Link to forward the information to a friend ( preformatted email in the user’s email product using mailto coding)

    • Address ( i.e. Advertiser’s)




As a User, I must be able to access [AdditionalContactInfo] near [ProductsandBrands] on the company profile page.


Note: For Desktop, as a User clicks on  ‘View details’ tab will expand and double click will collapse. For mobile/tablet it will be a ‘+’ or ‘-‘sign.
